workflow.name: Beginner lead finder using SerpAPI search
workflow.description:
This n8n workflow finds experts on **any topic**, scrapes their websites, and pulls out contact emails automatically. Core services used: **SerpAPI (google search)** ¬∑ **Apify (website crawler)** ¬∑ **OpenAI (GPT-4o email extraction)**. --- ## üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Setup & Execution ### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Run Workflow (Manual Trigger) | Node | Type | Purpose | |------|------|---------| | `Run Workflow` | Manual Trigger | Start the workflow on demand while you test. | --- ### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Set Your Topic | Node | Type | How to configure | |------|------|------------------| | `Set Topic` | **Set** | Add a string field **Topic** ‚Äì e.g. `"n8n"`. This keyword drives every subsequent step. | --- ### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Search Google (Results 1-10) | Node | Type | API Credential | |------|------|----------------| | `Search Google (top 10)` | **SerpAPI** | **Create SerpAPI credential**
1. Sign up ‚Üí copy API key ‚Üí n8n ‚Üí **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí SerpAPI** ‚Üí paste.
2. Select the credential in this node. | | **Key Params** | | | | `q` | | `={{ $json.Topic }} Expert` | | `location` | | Region code (ex `585069efee19ad271e9c9b36`) | | `additionalFields.start` | | `"10"` (Google position 1-10)| --- ### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Search Google (Results 11-20) | Node | Type | Notes | |------|------|-------| | `Search Google (11-20)` | **SerpAPI** (same credential) | Remove `start` or set to 20+ to fetch next page. | --- ### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Extract URL Lists | Node | Type | Script Purpose | |------|------|----------------| | `Extract Url` & `Extract Url 2` | **Code** | Loop `data.organic_results` ‚Üí output `{ title, link, displayed_link }` for each result. | --- ### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Combine Both Result Sets | Node | Type | Details | |------|------|---------| | `Append Results` | **Merge (combineAll)** | Merges arrays from steps 3 & 4 into a single list for processing. | --- ### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Loop Over Every URL | Node | Type | Configuration | |------|------|---------------| | `Loop Over Items1` | **Split In Batches** | Default batch = 1 (process one page at a time).
`onError = continueRegularOutput` keeps loop alive on failures. | --- ### 8Ô∏è‚É£ Scrape Webpage Content (Apify) | Node | Type | API Credential | |------|------|----------------| | `Scrape URL with apify` | **HTTP Request** | **Create Apify credential**
1. Sign up at https://console.apify.com
2. Account ‚Üí **API tokens** ‚Üí copy.
3. n8n ‚Üí **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí HTTP Query Auth** ‚Üí set query param `token=YOUR_TOKEN`. | | **Request Details** | | | | Method | POST | | URL | `https://api.apify.com/v2/acts/6sigmag~fast-website-content-crawler/run-sync-get-dataset-items` | | JSON Body | ```json { "startUrls": ["{{ $json.link }}"] } ``` | --- ### 9Ô∏è‚É£ Extract Email with OpenAI | Node | Type | API Credential | |------|------|----------------| | `Extract Email from webpage` | **LangChain Agent** | **Create OpenAI credential**
1. Generate key at https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys
2. n8n ‚Üí **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API** ‚Üí paste key. | | Prompt (system) | ```extract the email address from the text. if there is no email address, output null.``` | | **Output Parser** | `Structured Output Parser2` expects ‚Üí `{ "email": "address OR null" }` | --- ### üîü Loop Continues & Final Data - The extracted result returns to **Loop Over Items1** until every URL is processed. - **Typical final item JSON**: ```json { "title": "How to Build n8n Workflows", "link": "https://example.com", "email": "info@example.com" } üí° Optional Enhancements Idea How Save Leads Add a Google Sheets or Airtable node after the loop. Validate Emails Chain a ZeroBounce / Hunter.io verification API before saving. Parallel Crawling Increase SplitInBatches size (watch Apify rate limits). üôã‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Need More Help? parameters.content:
## üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Setup & Execution

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Run Workflow (Manual Trigger)
- **Node**: `Run Workflow`  
- **Type**: Manual Trigger  
- **Purpose**: Kick off the flow on demand.

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Set Your Topic
- **Node**: `Set Topic`  
- **Type**: Set  
- **Prerequisite**: None  
- **Configuration**:  
  - Add field **Topic** (string)  
  - Value: e.g. `"n8n"`

---

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Loop Over Each URL
- **Node**: `Loop Over Items1`  
- **Type**: SplitInBatches  
- **Purpose**: Process one URL at a time  
- **Error Handling**: `onError: continueRegularOutput`

---

### 8Ô∏è‚É£ Scrape Page Content with Apify
- **Node**: `Scrape URL with apify`  
- **Type**: HTTP Request  
- **Prerequisite / API Setup**:  
  1. Sign up at https://console.apify.com/  
  2. Create an API token (Account ‚Üí API tokens)  
  3. In n8n: **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí HTTP Query Auth**, set query param `token=YOUR_TOKEN`  
- **Request**:  
  - Method: POST  
  - URL: `https://api.apify.com/v2/acts/6sigmag~fast-website-content-crawler/run-sync-get-dataset-items`  
  - Body (JSON):  
    ```json
    {
      "startUrls": ["{{ $json.link }}"]
    }
    ```

---

### 9Ô∏è‚É£ Extract Email Address via AI
- **Node**: `Extract Email from webpage`  
- **Type**: LangChain Agent  
- **Prerequisite / API Setup**:  
  1. Create OpenAI API key at https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys  
  2. In n8n: **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**, paste key as **OpenAi account**  
- **Prompt**:

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Search Google Results (1‚Äì10)
- **Node**: `Search Google (top 10)`  
- **Type**: SerpAPI  
- **Prerequisite / API Setup**:  
  1. Sign up at https://serpapi.com/  
  2. Copy your API key  
  3. In n8n: **Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí SerpAPI**, paste key as **SerpAPI account**  
- **Parameters**:  
  - `q`: `={{ $json.Topic }} Expert`  
  - `location`: your region code (e.g., `"585069efee19ad271e9c9b36"`)  
  - `additionalFields.start`: `"10"` (for results 1‚Äì10)

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Search Google Results (11‚Äì20)
- **Node**: `Search Google (11-20)`  
- **Type**: SerpAPI  
- **Prerequisite**: Uses same **SerpAPI account** credential  
- **Parameters**:  
  - `q`: `={{ $json.Topic }} Expert`  
  - `location`: same as above  
  - omit `start` or set for results 11‚Äì20

---

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Extract URLs from Responses
- **Nodes**: `Extract Url` & `Extract Url 2`  
- **Type**: Code  
- **Purpose**: Parse `organic_results` to JSON items with `title`, `link`, and `displayed_link`  
- **Configuration**: Use JavaScript to map `data.organic_results` accordingly.

---

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Combine Both Result Sets
- **Node**: `Append Results`  
- **Type**: Merge (combineAll)  
- **Purpose**: Merge arrays from top 10 and 11‚Äì20 searches into one list.

---
